- To Run the server
- type `pip install -r requirements.txt` in the terminal.
- If no erros then ,
- type `python manage.py runserver` in the terminal
- Head over to `http://127.0.0.1:8000/`
- API Provider - openweathermap.org
- Docker image Building
  - `docker build -f Dockerfile .` (This will create an image with none name and tag)
  - `docker images` (copy the image_id)
  - `docker image tag <image_id> projectname:version` (eg for projectname:version -> weatherchecker:latest) default tag is latest.
  - `docker run --publish 8000:8000 projectname:version`
  - open docker desktop or just copy this link `http://0.0.0.0:8000/` and paste it in browser. 
  - If setup is successfull it will run the server.